The paper deals with the fine-grained complexity of problems in P, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions reductions and approximation algorithms, which are common topics in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses interactive proof systems, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
